div.p:
The project, which started as an offshoot of the Homer Multitext (

                        https://www.homermultitext.org/
                    ), has recently moved onto Transkribus, where we are currently migrating the transcription data.

To enable multimodal search functionality of texts and images, a Marqo index will be created from the material (

                        https://www.marqo.ai/
                    ). We will vectorize the cleaned texts and images with a multimodal open-source Large Language Model (LLM) to enable embedding-based retrieval (Pan et al. 2024) and index the vectors along with enriched metadata and full texts. As the captions to the emblems are notoriously extraneous from the content of the images, we will have to rely on section titles and full text content to generate appropriate keywords for each image. We will attempt to enrich the metadata using open source LLMs (e.g., LLAMA3) for unsupervised generation of keywords from the available text-image pairs for improved query results (Maragheh et al. 2023).
